Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Peel @carrots{2}, then cut into 3-inch lengths. Cut each piece into ⅓-inch-thick sticks (like French fries). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Core, seed, and dice @Roma tomato{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Zest @lime{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into halves. Cut @corn on the cob{1} into kernels until you have ⅓ cup corn. Drain and rinse half the @black beans{1/2%box} from the can and put in a large #bowl{} (use the rest of the corn and beans as you like).

> Beans: you're protein-packed, you're delicious. Did you know you're a great source of iron and magnesium? Everything about you is perfect.

Mash beans in a large bowl with a #potato masher{} or fork until mostly smooth but still a little chunky. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, 2 TBSP shallot, corn, and up to 1 TBSP jalapeño (use less to taste). Crack @eggs{1} into bowl and thoroughly combine (use the other egg as you like). Shape mixture into two ½-inch-thick patties.

> You can substitute the second egg if you prefer.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add burgers and cook until browned and firm, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. About 2 minutes before the burgers are done, sprinkle @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} onto tops of each and cover pan to melt cheese.

While burgers cook, combine tomato, 1 TBSP shallot, a squeeze of lime, and as much of the remaining jalapeño as you like in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. In another #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice, to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Split @brioche buns{2} in half and toast in oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. You can put the buns on sheet with carrots. Squeeze a little lime over carrots and divide between plates. Spread buns with half the crema and fill with burgers and salsa. Serve remaining crema on the side for dipping carrots into.